    thinking: "**Designing Component Layout**\n\nI am now designing the core components. I am prioritizing three key elements: `CardContenido.tsx`, `FeedReels.tsx`, and `FormularioIngreso.tsx`. The aim is to create a cyberpunk-inspired feed aesthetic, focusing on glassmorphic cards with neon glowing borders.\n\n\n**Prioritizing Card Design**\n\nI\'m now zeroing in on `CardContenido.tsx`. Each card needs to be vertically expansive for scroll-snapping, with a glassmorphic aesthetic. The borders will glow yellow for \'aqui\' and crimson for \'alla\'. Inside, I need a title, description, content type with icon, link, and delete button. I\'m pivoting towards a cyber-art mockup representing the content platform as a header, thinking of icons from `lucide-react` for platforms like YouTube.\n\n\n**Refining Content Icons**\n\nI\'ve been refining the content icons. I\'m leaning toward these for platform representation: `Youtube` for YouTube, `Instagram` for Instagram, `Linkedin` for LinkedIn, `Globe` for general web content, and now, crucially, `Video` or `Zap` for TikTok. I\'m increasingly drawn to `Zap` for TikTok due to its snackable content nature; it feels like a lightning bolt of engagement.\n\n\n**Implementing Card Backdrop**\n\nI am now focusing on the outer `div`. I\'ve added a `snap-start h-full w-full flex-shrink-0 flex flex-col justify-between relative bg-black border-b border-zinc-900 overflow-hidden` setup. Inside, I\'m working on a cyberpunk-style backdrop. I am trying dynamic CSS or Tailwind for the grid. A radial mask is going in for some cool effects! I am really liking the look of this cyberpunk grid.\n\n\n**Defining Card Contents**\n\nI\'m now determining the inner elements of `CardContenido.tsx`. Each card features a badge for content type and platform, styled icons, a title in large, bold, high-contrast text, a readable grey description, and a timestamp. I am also planning the buttons: \"Ver Contenido\" with an external link icon, and \"Eliminar\" with a trash icon. I am prioritizing a clean, high-performance implementation for mobile, considering simple CSS transitions over complex animation libraries.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I will create `/src/components/CardContenido.tsx` which handles the presentation of each curated link, using glassmorphic styling, glowing neon borders/shadows matching its category (\"Aqu\303\255\" / \"All\303\241\"), platform icons, metadata, an external navigation button, and a deletion trigger."
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 8
      nanos: 69935308
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
