  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Revising Style Presentation**\n\nI\'m currently focused on visually translating the provided screenshot\'s design into the application. The goal is to reshape the interface\'s style and structure, without changing the colors or functionality. \"Aqu\303\255\" will remain neon yellow, and \"All\303\241\" will stay crimson red. I\'m exploring how to best implement the aesthetic changes while maintaining user experience.\n\n\n**Analyzing Design Principles**\n\nI\'m now carefully analyzing the design principles from the screenshot. I\'ve noted the clean, high-contrast layout, specifically the light gray background and premium accents. I\'m focusing on the typography, which is a tall, stylized, condensed sans-serif font for \"DISCOVER\", and the use of rounded pills, clean icons and circular avatar and search button elements. The card backgrounds are also a key focus.\n\n\n**Implementing Visual Elements**\n\nI\'m now implementing the visual elements detailed in the design principles. Specifically, I\'m focusing on the highly rounded corners (thinking `rounded-[28px]` or `rounded-[32px]`), pill-shaped tags (like \"Last minute tours\" in a dusty rose, but for \"Aqu\303\255\" and \"All\303\241\"), and circular favorite buttons. I\'m also addressing the card content layout (white title, smaller description, metadata) and the ultra-premium glassy bottom navigation bar (`backdrop-blur-md`). The welcome screen\'s geometric font and pill-shaped action button are next.\n\n\n**Refining Visual Hierarchy**\n\nI\'m now integrating \"ROUTEMIND\", a large tall display font, to match the \"DISCOVER\" aesthetic, aiming for a high-end, editorial look. My focus is on the background: I\'m exploring a super clean light workspace (`bg-[#F3F4F6]` or `bg-zinc-50`), but implementing rich dark card containers, glass gradients, or a hybrid dark-light aesthetic, drawing inspiration from the screenshot\'s high-contrast card blocks for an ultra-modern feel. Deep background card colors, like dark or tinted grays, will support the neon accents.\n\n\n**Defining Font Imports**\n\nI\'m now focusing on defining the required font imports. I\'ve decided to use Inter as the primary sans-serif font and Oswald for the display headings, reflecting the screenshot\'s aesthetic. I\'m importing these fonts into `src/index.css`. The goal is to get that tall, condensed look for the main headings.\n\n\n**Integrating Font Declaration**\n\nI\'m now modifying `src/index.css` to declare the custom fonts using the Tailwind `@theme` directive, implementing Inter, Oswald, and JetBrains Mono as specified in the previous thought updates. I\'ve placed the font import at the top of the CSS file using the `@import url()` directive and then defined `--font-sans`, `--font-display`, and `--font-mono` under the `@theme` directive.\n\nI\'m now looking at the layout and cards of the screenshot, starting with the header. The title will be centered and styled with the extremely tall `font-display text-4xl tracking-wider text-black` style. An avatar circle will be on the left, and a search or filter button on the right. Filter options will be elegant rounded pills right under the header.\n\n\n**Styling Card Components**\n\nI\'m now fully immersed in card styling, concentrating on rounded containers and dynamic, abstract backgrounds, a concept that feels truly innovative for content curation. I\'m excited about the potential of generated gradients, linking card aesthetics to their content source, for example, a dark red-black YouTube gradient. The yellow and red pill-shaped tags (AQU\303\215 // BUENO and ALL\303\201 // EVITAR) are being styled with subtle tints. The circular action buttons and the text overlay (title and description) at the bottom are next.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I am going to update the CSS configuration to import the premium Google Fonts (**Oswald** for the tall, condensed display headlines and **Inter** for standard UI elements) and define the Tailwind CSS `@theme` variables for them, just like in the high-end application from the screenshot.\n\nLet\'s view the file `/src/index.css` to confirm its structure and then update it."
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 11
      nanos: 297632099
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
