  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Analyzing the Visuals**\n\nOkay, I\'ve started examining the visual layout, specifically aiming to replicate the screenshot. My current focus is the overall color scheme. I\'ve noted the light gray/off-white background and plan to set the simulator container\'s background to `#F3F4F6` to match that light theme.\n\n\n**Refining the Aesthetics**\n\nI\'m now diving deeper into the aesthetic details. I\'ve decided to refine the `App.tsx` container with either `bg-[#F3F4F6]` or `bg-zinc-100` for a light background. I\'m focusing on the smartphone frame\'s design, aiming for a premium black bezel and a clean white screen, and beautiful light minimalist backgrounds for the desktop simulator. The sidebar will have a dark, high-contrast panel, like ROUTEMIND, stating \"YOUR DESIGN CURATION / STARTS HERE\". I\'ll add a round star/flower glyph to the top of this sidebar.\n\n\n**Visualizing the Layout**\n\nI\'m now picturing the layout. I envision a circle on a dusty rose/peach background and will integrate a \"Sparkles\" glyph. I\'m also considering a large, condensed title like \"AQU\303\215 / ALL\303\201\" or \"ROUTEMIND,\" plus a stylish \"Let\'s start\" button for the Bottom Sheet. The desktop layout\'s left sidebar will mirror the phone mockup\'s ROUTEMIND welcome view, either with a dark mountain/cyber style or a gradient with glowing borders. The central content feed will follow the DISCOVER view\'s clean white aesthetic with rounded cards and gradients.\n\n\n**Defining Card Gradients**\n\nI\'m now zeroing in on the aesthetic of the curated item cards. I\'ve decided to give each card a distinct, refined abstract background. These will be based on the platform or category, with five gorgeous gradients available that evoke locations or themes like Tokyo or Paris. Each card will have a high-contrast image overlay and dark drop shadow for optimal text readability. I\'ve listed gradient examples like \"Sunset Tokyo\" or \"Cyber Kyoto,\" to use on our cards.\n\n\n**Refining the Card Details**\n\nI\'m now focusing on the individual card design elements, specifically replicating the \"Last minute tours\" pill. I envision a dusty-rose or light-yellow capsule, with elegant letter spacing, using the `rounded-full` and background color classes mentioned in my notes. For the top-right, I\'m thinking of a circular heart/like button, perhaps with a heart icon for \"Aqu\303\255\" and a warning icon for \"All\303\241,\" toggling the status or acting as a delete button with a tooltip. I\'ll need big, bold white text for the titles, with smaller text for the description. Finally, I\'ll incorporate a platform indicator on the right side of the card.\n\n\n**Implementing the UI**\n\nI\'m now focused on implementing the UI elements. I\'m excited about the transparent, pill-shaped action button with the glass style \342\200\223 it\'s a clever design choice! I\'m updating `CardContenido.tsx` to incorporate this, aiming for high fidelity. I\'ll also inspect `FeedReels.tsx`, making sure its light gray/white background matches the mockup, and that the feed header includes the circular avatar, title (\"EXPLORAR\"), and search/plus button, just as in the design.\n\n\n**Designing the Feed Controls**\n\nI\'m now zeroing in on the feed controls, I\'ll enhance `FeedReels.tsx` to include an avatar and buttons for search/add. The title will have an `xl font-bold uppercase text-black` style. I\'ll add a floating dock at the bottom of the feed that\'s translucent, like in the screenshot. It will be styled with `backdrop-blur-xl bg-white/60 border border-zinc-200/50 shadow-[0_10px_30px_rgba(0,0,0,0.08)] rounded-[32px] absolute bottom-6 left-6 right-6 h-16 flex items-center justify-around px-4 z-40`. The dock will include icons for \"Ver Todo\" (Compass) and a stats summary (Layers or Database).\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I am going to completely redesign the `/src/components/CardContenido.tsx` component to match the visual layout shown in the screenshot. \n\nThe new card design includes:\n- **Full-cover premium backgrounds**: Highly-refined mesh gradients (Sunset Orange, Cyber Cyan, Golden Rose, Crimson Fire, and Slate Grey) that simulate the professional imagery of Tokyo and Paris.\n- **Top left capsule pill**: Styled exactly like the *\"Last minute tours\"* pill in the photo, showing custom tags like **AQU\303\215 // INSPIRACI\303\223N** (soft yellow glass) and **ALL\303\201 // EVITAR** (soft crimson glass).\n- **Top right circular trigger**: A rounded glass bookmark/delete icon that fits the aesthetics.\n- **Title & description layout**: Positioned elegantly at the bottom with high contrast, paired with the platform label on the right side (styled like the pricing metadata in the screenshot).\n- **Let\'s Start styled button**: Transparent glass pill action button to open original links.\n\nLet\'s write this beautiful component."
