  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Analyzing the Design**\n\nI\'m currently focused on replicating the aesthetic of the ROUTEMIND startup screen. Specifically, I\'m examining the black/dark charcoal background, striving to capture its breathtaking quality. My objective is to create a Left Sidebar for the desktop that emulates this impressive design.\n\n\n**Crafting the Visuals**\n\nI\'m now implementing the design details. I\'ve chosen a rich dark background gradient and am building the circular glyph, thinking \"Sparkles\" or \"Compass\" in a pinkish-orange circle. The display text, \"AQU\303\215 & ALL\303\201\" or \"ROUTEMIND\", will use a strong font with wide tracking. Lastly, I\'m exploring a stylized graphic for the center, leaning towards a futuristic mesh built with styled boxes.\n\n\n**Implementing the Welcome Screen**\n\nI\'m now integrating the \"Welcome Screen\" design into the Left Sidebar. I\'m focusing on the typography, specifically \"Bienvenido al Curador\" or \"Tus ideas en un solo lugar\" in huge bold typography. Underneath the title, I\'ll be integrating \"Documenta patrones de excelencia visual e ingenier\303\255a limpia junto a antipatrones cr\303\255ticos de producci\303\263n.\" And the final button will be, a transparent pill-shaped start button: \"A\303\261adir Hallazgo\", which will open the bottom sheet modal inside the central feed! This design is incredibly elegant, and will be perfect for the desktop layout of the Left Sidebar.\n\n\n**Refining the App Layout**\n\nI\'m now diving deep into `App.tsx`, aiming for a majestic rewrite to handle the desktop and mobile views seamlessly. The goal is to perfectly emulate the ROUTEMIND welcome screen, with a black background and abstract grid. I envision a coral circular badge at the top, followed by towering typography \"AQU\303\215 / ALL\303\201,\" and a stunning vector background mimicking mountain ranges. This modularity will allow the user to see the discover screen as a desktop layout or swiping in a mobile frame.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I am now going to completely rewrite `/src/App.tsx` to build the hybrid layout that represents both mockups of the user\'s screenshot:\n\n1. **Desktop Left Panel (Mockup 1 - ROUTEMIND Welcome Screen)**:\n   - **Top Badge**: A soft pastel coral round badge with a custom spinning abstract vector emblem, matching the top circle icon from the screenshot\'s left screen.\n   - **Towering Title**: **\"AQU\303\215 & ALL\303\201\"** rendered in high-impact, bold, condensed Oswald display lettering.\n   - **Vector Art Layer**: A sleek, minimal, high-contrast dark visual grid representing mountain-mesh topology, created using absolute positioning, dark gradients, and fine lines.\n   - **Typography Block**: Large heavy-weight headers *\"Your Curation Starts Here\"* and *\"Tus ideas en un solo lugar\"*.\n   - **Action Pill**: A transparent bordered pill-button styled like *\"Let\'s start\"*, which directly triggers the creation form inside the feed.\n   - **Database Statistics**: Elegantly embedded at the very bottom in micro-typography.\n\n2. **Smartphone Simulator (Mockup 2 - DISCOVER Feed)**:\n   - A bright, beautiful device mock with highly-polished bezels and status bar that center the content feed.\n   - Toggling to full desktop breaks the device mock and scales the feed into an expansive fullscreen dashboard.\n\nLet\'s write this beautiful file now."
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 5
      nanos: 954324983
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
