  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Designing Search Toggle**\n\nI\'m currently focused on designing an elegant search toggle for the header. My latest idea is to use a Search icon button that, when pressed, gracefully morphs into a rounded glass text input field. This input will occupy space to seamlessly integrate the search functionality. I am envisioning that this design will be activated by `isSearchActive` being true.\n\n\n**Refining Search Bar Design**\n\nI\'ve been iterating on the search bar\'s visual integration. My current focus is on a layout where the avatar and a search trigger coexist on the left. The title, or an input field when the search is active, would be centered. A search trigger on the left of the title, and the add trigger on the right gives a nice symmetric look.\n\n\n**Implementing Absolute Overlay**\n\nI\'ve decided to implement a high-fidelity absolute overlay for the search bar, animating it from the top of the header when `isSearchActive` is true. This ensures the design is fully contained, responsive, and works seamlessly across mobile and desktop. I am checking the header\'s code structure to ensure proper integration.\n\n\n**Finalizing Search Input Field**\n\nI\'ve just added a clear \"X\" button and the actual search input field. Now, the full search bar is working! It expands beautifully from the top of the header. It handles the input query and clearing it with a click on the \"X\". The placeholder text is also displaying nicely! I\'ve incorporated the autoFocus and ensured proper styling of the input and the clear button.\n\n\n**Refining Header Components**\n\nI\'m now focusing on refining the header\'s components beyond the search bar. My intention is to incorporate a user avatar with a status indicator, ensuring it integrates gracefully with the existing layout. I\'m also ensuring the title\'s aesthetics are spot-on. I\'m trying to decide on the best hover and press styles.\n\n\n**Integrating Search and Add**\n\nI\'m now integrating the search toggle with the \"Add\" button for new resources. I\'ve updated the button styles for search and add and am making sure the layout adapts fluidly, with a consistent visual language. The goal is a clean, intuitive layout with buttons for search and adding new resources.\n\n\n"
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 12
      nanos: 95255186
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
